## Trends
HN is oscillating between enthusiasm for production-grade AI tools and anxiety about their influence. The front page is dominated by deep dives into Claude, RL progress, and AI documentaries, while the newest queue floods with build-your-own-LLM experiences, Gemini tooling, safety loopholes, and debates about whether the model race is a bubble. Several posts (e.g., the RL efficiency critique, “AI doesn't add up if you neglect mathematicians,” and “OpenAI's lead under pressure…”) highlight skepticism about reckless scaling even as hobbyists ship image enhancers, code assistants, and language workflows.
